Preheat your oven to 220°C/200°C fan/gas mark 7.

Chop the @potatoes{450%g} into 2cm wide wedges (no need to peel).

Pop the wedges onto a large #baking tray{}. Drizzle with @oil{for drizzling}, 
sprinkle over the @dried rosemary{1} and season with @salt{for seasoning} 
and @pepper{for seasoning}. Toss to coat, then spread out in a single layer.

> Use two baking trays if necessary.

When the oven is hot, roast on the top shelf until golden, ~{25-35%minutes}. 
Turn halfway through.

Meanwhile, quarter, core and grate the @apple{1/2}(grated) (no need to peel).

In a large #bowl{}, combine the apple, @panko breadcrumbs{10%g} and 
@salt{1/4%tsp}, then add the @British pork mince{240%g}. Season with pepper and 
mix together with your hands. Roll into even-sized balls, then shape into 
1cm thick burgers, 1 per person.

> The burgers will shrink a little during cooking.
> IMPORTANT: Wash your hands and equipment after handling raw mince.

Pop the burgers onto another baking tray alongside the rashers. Add the 
@British streaky bacon{4}(rashers). Bake on the middle shelf of your oven 
until the burgers are cooked through and the bacon is crispy, 
~{12-15%minutes}.

> IMPORTANT: The burgers are cooked when no longer pink in the middle. Cook 
> bacon thoroughly.

Meanwhile, grate the @mature cheddar cheese{30%g}.

When the burgers are cooked, carefully place the cheese on top of the burgers 
and pop back into the oven until the cheese has melted, ~{2-3%minutes}.

At the same time, halve the @burger buns{2}. Pop them onto a baking tray and 
into oven to warm through, ~{2-3%minutes}. Put the bacon rashers aside on a 
#plate{} lined with #kitchen paper{}.

Just before serving, add the @wild rocket{20%g} to a medium bowl. Drizzle with 
the @balsamic glaze{12%ml}. Toss to evenly coat the rocket.

When everything's ready, spread the @apple and sage jelly{25%ml} over the bun 
bases. Top with the cheesy burgers, 2 bacon rashers and bun lids.

Serve your pork and apple burger with the rosemary wedges and salad alongside.

> Enjoy!